The paper discusses the measurement of inconsistency in databases and proposes a measure that is both rational and computationally tractable. This topic falls under the category of databases (cs.DB) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI) as it involves knowledge representation and reasoning. The paper also discusses progress indicators, which could fall under the category of machine learning (cs.LG) or data structures and algorithms (cs.DS). Finally, the paper discusses the interplay between database tuples, integrity constraints, and repairing operations, which could fall under the category of software engineering (cs.SE).
